---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, GITHUB_URL, LINKEDIN_URL } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Karthik Mahalingam — Principal Engineering Manager at Microsoft. 19+ years in distributed systems, now focused on AI compliance, risk, and safety."
		/>
		<style>
			main {
				max-width: 720px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 0 1.5rem;
			}

			.about-header {
				padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
				border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
			}

			.about-header h1 {
				font-size: 2rem;
				font-weight: 700;
				margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
				color: #111;
			}

			.about-header .role {
				font-size: 1.05rem;
				color: #555;
				margin: 0;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}

			.about-section {
				padding: 2rem 0;
				border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
			}

			.about-section:last-of-type {
				border-bottom: none;
				padding-bottom: 4rem;
			}

			.about-section h2 {
				font-size: 1.15rem;
				font-weight: 600;
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
				color: #111;
				font-family: sans-serif;
			}

			.about-section p {
				font-size: 1rem;
				line-height: 1.8;
				color: #444;
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
			}

			.about-section p:last-child {
				margin-bottom: 0;
			}

			.connect-links {
				display: flex;
				gap: 1rem;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
				margin-top: 1.25rem;
			}

			.connect-links a {
				color: #111;
				padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem;
				border: 1px solid #ccc;
				border-radius: 4px;
				text-decoration: none;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				font-family: sans-serif;
			}

			.connect-links a:hover {
				border-color: #111;
			}

			.cta-box {
				background: #f8f8f8;
				border: 1px solid #eee;
				border-radius: 6px;
				padding: 1.5rem;
				margin-top: 1.5rem;
			}

			.cta-box p {
				margin: 0 0 1rem;
			}

			.cta-box a {
				display: inline-block;
				background: #111;
				color: #fff;
				padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
				border-radius: 4px;
				text-decoration: none;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				font-family: sans-serif;
			}

			.cta-box a:hover {
				background: #333;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-header">
				<h1>About Me</h1>
				<p class="role">
					Principal Engineering Manager at Microsoft. 19+ years building systems that scale.
				</p>
			</div>

			<section class="about-section">
				<h2>Background</h2>
				<p>
					I'm Karthik Mahalingam. I've spent nearly two decades building and leading engineering
					teams across developer tools, semiconductor systems, and enterprise cloud platforms. My
					career started at Syncfusion, where I went from writing code to leading product strategy.
					I then spent close to a decade at KLA, managing engineering teams that built
					high-throughput systems for the semiconductor industry. In 2021, I joined Microsoft.
				</p>
				<p>
					At Microsoft, I lead engineering for Purview Data Lifecycle Management — building the
					services that handle data retention, compliance, and governance across millions of
					mailboxes and thousands of enterprise tenants. Over the past couple of years, my work has
					increasingly moved toward AI: deploying multi-agent LLM systems, building RAG/CAG
					pipelines, and applying AI to compliance automation at enterprise scale.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="about-section">
				<h2>What this blog is about</h2>
				<p>
					Latent Mesh is where I think out loud about the problems I work on and around — AI
					agents, system evaluations, safety, privacy, and the distributed systems patterns that
					underpin all of it. These are notes from someone who builds these systems for a living,
					not a researcher writing from the outside. The questions here tend to be practical: how
					do you govern agents at scale? How do you evaluate AI systems before shipping them? What
					does compliance actually look like when AI is in the loop?
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="about-section">
				<h2>Let's talk</h2>
				<p>
					I'm open to conversations with founders, engineering leaders, and companies navigating
					AI compliance, regulatory risk, and safety. If you're building in this space and want to
					think through the hard problems together, I'd welcome the conversation.
				</p>
				<div class="cta-box">
					<p>
						Reach out to discuss AI compliance, risk, regulatory strategy, or safety engineering.
					</p>
					<a href={LINKEDIN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						Message me on LinkedIn
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class="connect-links">
					<a href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
					<a href={LINKEDIN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
